entries.message:
Patch Set 1:

> could you please link an example that shows the difference in the
 > generated output?

When installing graphadmin, before and after the change was made, we compared the sorted list of operations, and found all cases where we missed a singular API operation with the before code, with the code change the operation was included:

/nodes/aggregate-routes
/nodes/aggregate-routes/aggregate-route/{route-id}
/nodes/allotted-resources
/nodes/availability-zones
/nodes/classes-of-service
/nodes/cloud-regions
/nodes/collections
/nodes/collections/collection/{collection-id}
/nodes/complexes
/nodes/complexes/complex/{physical-location-id}

and after

 /nodes/aggregate-routes
 /nodes/aggregate-routes/aggregate-route/{route-id}
 /nodes/allotted-resources
 /nodes/allotted-resources/allotted-resource/{id}
 /nodes/availability-zones
 /nodes/availability-zones/availability-zone/{availability-zone-name}
 /nodes/classes-of-service
 /nodes/class-of-service/{cos}
 /nodes/cloud-regions
 /nodes/cloud-regions/cloud-region/{cloud-owner}/{cloud-region-id}
 /nodes/collections
 /nodes/collections/collection/{collection-id}
 /nodes/complexes
 /nodes/complexes/complex/{physical-location-id}
